      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But instead, the strategy made the program vulnerable. ‚ÄúIf they had forced the Supreme Court to make a decision that didn‚Äôt just stop [the cancellation program] but actually forced the court to reenact debt, I think that would be a different situation,‚Äù said Herrine, because of the logistical challenge and potential political backlash of reimposing already-canceled debt.",
